00:42:36.550 --> 00:42:39.500
of the early adapters
of GIS technology,

00:42:39.500 --> 00:42:42.660
and there's still a tremendous
amount of work that can be done

00:42:42.660 --> 00:42:47.290
in forestry in an area that
have some expertise in,

00:42:47.290 --> 00:42:51.180
and as you look at
all the other uses,

00:42:51.180 --> 00:42:52.760
it's just, it's pretty amazing.

00:42:52.760 --> 00:42:55.900
I had a fascinating conversation
with National Geographic,

00:42:55.900 --> 00:42:59.910
probably it's been
within the last two years,

00:42:59.910 --> 00:43:03.380
and they were talking about all
the mapping that they're doing,

00:43:03.380 --> 00:43:07.040
the different kinds of mapping,
and it just makes your head spin

00:43:07.040 --> 00:43:09.040
to think that there's
that much data out there

00:43:09.040 --> 00:43:11.400
and all the analysis
we can do with it,

00:43:11.400 --> 00:43:14.340
and I think it could
actually affect policy,

00:43:14.340 --> 00:43:18.180
because you would hope
that lawmakers are looking

00:43:18.180 --> 00:43:21.380
at the data that's available to
make the most informed decision,

00:43:21.380 --> 00:43:25.550
and if you can get better data
in a more real-time situation,

00:43:25.550 --> 00:43:30.000
then you can make
better decisions.

00:43:30.000 --> 00:43:33.630
I was just looking at a map

00:43:33.630 --> 00:43:35.950
on wildland urban
interfaces this morning,

00:43:35.950 --> 00:43:38.820
which is all geospatial
data, with the wildfires

00:43:38.820 --> 00:43:41.440
that are happening
out in California,

00:43:41.440 --> 00:43:45.600
and we're seeing more and
more with warming temperatures

00:43:45.600 --> 00:43:50.150
and drier conditions and more
people moving into the WUI,

00:43:50.150 --> 00:43:52.840
as we call it, wildland-urban
interface.

00:43:52.840 --> 00:43:54.350
I think we're going to have

00:43:54.350 --> 00:43:59.270
to make some definite policy
changes and has some leadership

00:43:59.270 --> 00:44:01.590
in the federal government
to address that government,

00:44:01.590 --> 00:44:03.950
and GIS will be critical
in doing that.

00:44:03.950 --> 00:44:05.250
So, it's everywhere.

00:44:05.250 --> 00:44:08.620
It affects all the
parts of our lives.

00:44:08.620 --> 00:44:11.430
People just -- I don't think the
general public realizes that,

00:44:11.430 --> 00:44:13.730
how much they actually use it.

00:44:16.510 --> 00:44:21.040
[ Female Speaking off Mic ]

00:44:21.040 --> 00:44:22.620
Yeah, you would think so.

00:44:22.620 --> 00:44:27.340
I served in my state
legislature, and I was there

00:44:27.340 --> 00:44:32.100
