01:49:55.540 --> 01:49:59.970
out what databases exist,
because we're looking at it

01:49:59.970 --> 01:50:05.040
from the geographic location
within the work of fiction.

01:50:05.040 --> 01:50:07.860
But there are other databases
out there that we need

01:50:07.860 --> 01:50:09.730
to incorporate their
information.

01:50:09.730 --> 01:50:13.250
So, going back to that Illinois
Writers Project, there's a lot

01:50:13.250 --> 01:50:15.620
of great data that they have

01:50:15.620 --> 01:50:18.600
that would inform this
particular project.

01:50:18.600 --> 01:50:21.170
So, trying to take a
look at the data sets

01:50:21.170 --> 01:50:23.970
that already exist
within the field.

01:50:23.970 --> 01:50:26.740
So, some of the ones that
we're looking at are Amazon,

01:50:26.740 --> 01:50:33.100
Overdrive, GoodReads, which is
also Amazon, Barnes &amp; Noble,

01:50:33.100 --> 01:50:40.040
in terms of databases that
exist and what would be involved

01:50:40.040 --> 01:50:43.120
with merging and
sharing that data?

01:50:43.120 --> 01:50:45.590
So, some of the next
steps that we are taking,

01:50:45.590 --> 01:50:49.030
we will have another junior
fellow here this summer,

01:50:49.030 --> 01:50:53.160
and this junior fellow, most
likely, will come from --

01:50:53.160 --> 01:50:58.200
