02:09:36.250 --> 02:09:40.350
as a [speaking off mic], and
you know, we worked nonstop

02:09:40.350 --> 02:09:43.840
on the K-12 project,
and the thing to know

02:09:43.840 --> 02:09:45.530
about it is geography is one

02:09:45.530 --> 02:09:53.510
of nine core academic subjects
identified in the federal law

02:09:53.510 --> 02:10:01.010
under the Elementary and
Secondary Education Act,

02:10:01.010 --> 02:10:05.370
as the core subjects that
students should focus

02:10:05.370 --> 02:10:06.670
on [speaking off mic].

02:10:06.670 --> 02:10:07.970
But of course, we
live in a country

02:10:07.970 --> 02:10:12.710
where state standards are set
at the state and local level,

02:10:12.710 --> 02:10:14.830
and the federal government can
really only have an influence

02:10:14.830 --> 02:10:16.130
by making the states
follow the money.

02:10:16.130 --> 02:10:17.430
And even though geography
has always been a core

02:10:17.430 --> 02:10:18.730
academic subject.

